<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by yrogerg on 11-06-2000 09:46 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Please read a statement through before responding to it. It appears that the bulk of responses, starting with muse, are not to Gordons posting, but to a percieved insult to high/low characters. Gordon said nothing in his post that indicated he preferred one over the other. His complaint, which I agree with, was that there is a wider variety of things to challenge the lower levels than the upper levels. This is undeniably true, primarily due to the fact that EVERYTHING is a challenge to the low level character. The higher you get, the harder it is to find a challenging opponent that isn't an indestructable killing machine. At 11th level I have a very hard time finding something to fight that is not so easy I get no exp or cash off it, yet not so tough it just kills me right off. Oh sure, there are wolves and bears to fight, but I am a ranger, it is implied that I exist to preserve nature and play Buffalo Bill and kill every bear in the woods just because they are there. I simply can't justify my defender of the forests attacking a creature that cons as frindly to me and will leave me alone if I do likewise. The majority of players at my level find that killing bears solo is the quickest way to level, so I have a hard time finding a group anymore. Does this seem stupid to anyone? If the game is about Role-Playing, then I should be fighting the bear-killers, not the bears.If it is just about getting my level up, then I should just kill everything in sight, and what's the point of being a ranger and choosing a diety and NPC guild that claims to be defenders of wildlife? When I was below 10th level I was always being attacked by orcs in the forest, and had the sense that I was defending my fellow elves from a real threat. Now, it seems I must become the despoiler and kill friendly animals just so I can get exp. The Role-Playing element is totally missing now. What was a great game where everyone in a party had to function as a team and back each other up, or everyone died, has devolved into boring hack-and whack click the button until monster is dead and repeat. I am no longer a person playing a role, but a set of numbers that must go up.This is very boring and pointless to me.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
